4.  Briefly explain the TTL (Time To Live) concept.Certainly! To keep things simple and straightforward, we can create a lightweight caching wrapper around `localStorage`. This approach requires no external libraries and handles the basics: storing data, setting an expiration time (TTL), and checking validity before returning data.

### 1. The Simple Cache Utility

Here is a clean, reusable class that handles the storage logic and expiration automatically.

```javascript
// SimpleCache.js
class SimpleCache {
  /**
   * @param {string} prefix - A prefix for localStorage keys to avoid collisions.
   */
  constructor(prefix = 'app_cache_') {
    this.prefix = prefix;
  }

  /**
   * Stores data with a specific Time-To-Live (TTL).
   * @param {string} key - The cache key (e.g., city name).
   * @param {any} data - The data to store.
   * @param {number} ttlMinutes - How long the cache should last in minutes.
   */
  set(key, data, ttlMinutes = 10) {
    const item = {
      data: data,
      expiry: Date.now() + (ttlMinutes * 60 * 1000),
    };
    try {
      localStorage.setItem(this.prefix + key, JSON.stringify(item));
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error saving to cache:', error);
      // Optional: Clear cache if storage is full
      this.clear();
    }
  }

  /**
   * Retrieves data if it exists and hasn't expired.
   * @param {string} key - The cache key.
   * @returns {any|null} - The cached data or null if invalid/expired.
   */
  get(key) {
    const itemStr = localStorage.getItem(this.prefix + key);

    // Return null if no item found
    if (!itemStr) return null;

    const item = JSON.parse(itemStr);

    // Check if the item has expired
    if (Date.now() > item.expiry) {
      localStorage.removeItem(this.prefix + key);
      return null;
    }

    return item.data;
  }

  /**
   * Clears all items with the specific prefix.
   */
  clear() {
    Object.keys(localStorage)
      .filter(key => key.startsWith(this.prefix))
      .forEach(key => localStorage.removeItem(key));
  }
}

// Export a single instance for easy use
const cache = new SimpleCache('weather_app_');
```

